article.headline: Stony Brook 56, Wagner 55
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Antwan Hardy scored 14 of his 20 points in the second half to lead Stony Brook to a 56-55 victory over Wagner on Thursday night, extending the Seahawks' losing streak to eight. Sean Munson scored 14 points and pulled down 11 rebounds, and Mark Porter added 12 points for the Seahawks (1-9). Wagner closed to within 51-50 on a 3-pointer by De Earnest McLemore at 4:38. Hardy's jumper increased the lead to 56-50 at 1:39, but Porter made a layup that got Wagner to within 56-54 with 37.1 seconds left. Munson then missed the front end of a two-shot foul to complete the scoring with 25.3 seconds remaining. Stony Brook (5-4) held a 27-21 halftime lead, but fell behind 38-31 at 13:48 of the second half on Munson's rebound basket. The Seawolves then went on a 14-4 run to take a 45-42 lead on John Paul Kobryn's jumper at 8:30. Hardy led the comeback with seven points.
